## Data Format Requirements
When adding new airfoil data:
- Reynolds numbers: `Vector{Float64}` (e.g., [5e4, 1e5, 2e5, 5e5, 1e6])
- Angles of attack: `Vector{Float64}` in radians (use `deg2rad.()`)
- Coefficients: `Matrix{Float64}` with dimensions [n_alpha, n_reynolds]
- Always include source citation string

## Testing Strategy
All new airfoils must have tests:
- Basic functionality (returns correct struct)
- Physical constraints (Cd > 0, etc.)
- Symmetric airfoil properties (Cl ≈ 0 at α = 0)
- Known values from literature (if available)

## Usage Example
```julia
using NACAData

# Get performance at specific conditions
result = get_naca_performance("0012", 1e5, deg2rad(5))
println("Cl = ", result.cl_ND)  # Lift coefficient
println("Cd = ", result.cd_ND)  # Drag coefficient
println("L/D = ", result.cl_ND / result.cd_ND)

# List available airfoils
available = list_available_airfoils()  # ["0012"]
```

